Parliament, Tuesday, 19 May 2020 – The Standing Committee on Appropriations will tomorrow receive a briefing from the National Treasury and the Land and Agricultural Development Bank of South Africa on issues affecting the entity.
	
	Details of the meeting are as follows:
	Date: Wednesday, 20 May 2020
	Time: 09:00 am
	
	Meanwhile, the Select Committee on Appropriations is scheduled to consider the negotiating mandates of provinces on the Division of Revenue Bill [B3 — 2020].
	
	Details of the meeting are as follows:
	Date: Wednesday, 20 May 2020
	Time: 09:00 am
	
	Members of the media who would like to be part of the meetings to observe may forward their contact details to Mr Mlindi Mpindi on +27817167329 for inclusion in the Parliament Communications Service Whatsapp group, where login details will be shared.
	
	Members of the public may get involved and follow committee sittings live on Parliament TV (DStv Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
